# Todo App (Flask)

This is the first full stack app i have ever made. 

When you open the app you will ahve to create a new account. 
but if you then close the window and then open the app again your account won't be there because SQlite db is not persistent as a new one is made everytime the app is run.
I should have use postgre. i will next time

A full-stack task management web application built with Flask, SQLite, and vanilla JavaScript.

## Features
- User authentication (register/login/logout)
- Create, edit, delete tasks
- Mark tasks as complete
- Search/filter tasks
- Pagination system
- REST API backend
- Responsive frontend

## Tech Stack
- Python (Flask)
- SQLite
- HTML/CSS
- JavaScript (Vanilla)

## Project Structure
- routes/ → API + auth routes
- models/ → database models
- utils/ → helper functions
- static/ → frontend JS & CSS
- templates/ → HTML pages

## Setup (local)
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py